  <article class="prose-tool space-y-7">
    <h1>Passport Photo Size in India</h1>
    <p>
      A common passport-style photo size used in India is 35mm x 45mm. Different visa, exam and identity
      workflows may ask for different sizes, so always check the exact official instruction before submission.
    </p>
    <h2>Quick reference</h2>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr><th>Common size</th><td>35mm x 45mm</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Digital equivalent</th><td>About 413 x 531 px at 300 DPI</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Background</th><td>Usually white or light background</td></tr>
        <tr><th>Format</th><td>JPG is accepted by most portals</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h2>How to prepare the photo</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Use a clear front-facing photo with even lighting.</li>
      <li>Crop around the head and shoulders according to the portal instructions.</li>
      <li>Resize to the required dimensions and file size.</li>
      <li>Preview the final image before upload or print.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>
      Use the <a href="/tools/passport-photo-maker/">Passport Photo Maker</a> to create a printable photo sheet, or
      use <a href="/tools/image-resize/">Image Resize</a> for exact pixel dimensions.
    </p>
  </article>
